  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Data Structure**\n\nI\'m currently focused on defining the pure data structure and calculation functions for this platform-independent prototype single-page app. Avoiding any HTML/UI considerations for now; I\'m isolating the data core.\n\n\n**Refining Project Scope**\n\nI\'ve shifted focus to defining the technical scope. I\'m taking a step back to confirm that the prototype is intended to use modular Javascript or Typescript. My understanding is that the goal is a React TypeScript project that will not include integration of external services, UI, or real-time functionalities. The objective is to produce a local, isolated, store.js module.\n\n\n**Clarifying Requirements for Logic**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the core logic and data structures for this CO2 calculator. I\'ve re-reviewed the requirements, and I\'m designing a JavaScript object to model the initial state. The functions `calculateTotalCO2()` and `saveToLocalStorage()` are now defined. I will keep the project as an isolated and platform-independent module.\n\n\n**Re-aligning with Intent**\n\nI\'m revisiting the initial user prompt and project goals to ensure strict adherence. It\'s clear the user explicitly requests only the state/logic file as code. Although an amazing UI would be great, the directive is \"build exactly what the user described, nothing more, nothing less,\" and that means just `store.js` or `store.ts` module. The focus is now solely on the requested code output.\n\n\n**Re-evaluating Project Constraints**\n\nI\'m wrestling with the project\'s boundaries, particularly whether an interactive demo (even if just for validation) aligns with the explicitly stated \"no UI/HTML/CSS\" requirement. I\'m re-reading the directives, translating the German phrases to assess the permissibility of a demo that *uses* but doesn\'t *constitute* the UI. Ultimately, the question is whether demonstrating the store, in the same project, to the user, would represent a breach of the explicitly-defined scope. I\'m focusing on \"strict, modular JavaScript code\" as the core deliverable.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 7
      nanos: 987005396
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
