  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Crafting Store Logic**\n\nI\'m now focusing on writing the core `store.js` logic, aiming for stricter, modular JavaScript code. My goal is to create a solid foundation for the module, as requested.\n\n\n**Refining Data Structures**\n\nI\'m now implementing the `store.js` module as an ES6 module, creating `src/store.js`. I\'m focusing on a clean, state-oriented design. I\'m starting by defining a clear `initialCO2State` object and functions: `calculateTotalCO2(state)`, `saveToLocalStorage(state)`, and `loadFromLocalStorage()` to restore. The key is now ensuring that calculations are performed correctly with the user-provided data.\n\n\n**Defining Emission Factors**\n\nI\'ve formalized the emission factors as an `EMISSION_FACTORS` object, now ensuring I\'ve captured the CO2 data precisely. The `INITIAL_STATE` has been refined. I\'m starting to build a robust `transport`, `diet`, and `consumption` structure. I\'m focusing on kilometers driven, vegan/meat days, and kilowatt-hour values, aiming to build a state with granular fields.\n\n\n**Structuring Core Calculations**\n\nI\'m now integrating vegan day logic into the `diet` section, including electricity usage for consumption. I\'m focusing on descriptive JSDoc comments. I\'m building a robust system using ES6 ESM export syntax, and calculation functions. I\'m creating `src/store.js` using `create_file` as an ES6 module. I\'m drafting the `store.js` with the foundational data structures and emission factors.\n\n\n**Calculating CO2 Impact**\n\nI\'m now incorporating detailed emission factors and the initial state. I\'m focusing on accurately capturing the CO2 data, structuring `transport`, `diet`, and `consumption` with kilometers, vegan days, and kilowatt-hours. I\'ve defined `EMISSION_FACTORS` and `INITIAL_STATE`, ensuring precise calculations based on user input. I\'m aiming for a robust system with clearly defined `calculateTotalCO2(state)` to measure total CO2.\n\n\n**Defining Calculation Logic**\n\nI\'m now focusing on implementing the CO2 calculation functions. I\'m structuring them into `transportTotal`, `dietTotal`, and `electricityCO2`, then calculating the total, rounded to two decimal places. The functions are being written using a modular structure with clear variable names and comments. I\'m focusing on ensuring accuracy in my implementation.\n\n\n**Implementing Storage Functions**\n\nI\'m now integrating the `saveToLocalStorage` and `loadFromLocalStorage` functions into the `store.js` module, focused on browser storage. I\'m ensuring robust error handling for local storage operations, including default values to prevent failures. I\'m validating loaded data against the `INITIAL_STATE` structure, and incorporating robust error handling.\n\n\n**Validating Stored Data**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the data loading process. I\'m making it robust by validating loaded data against the `INITIAL_STATE`, and handling potential errors. The goal is to gracefully handle any issues in local storage, providing a default state as a fallback to prevent failures, now including type checking for numerical data.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 17
      nanos: 141309661
    }
