    thinking: "**Considering Styling the App**\n\nI\'m currently focused on how to best style `/src/App.tsx`. I\'ve identified several key imports from `./store.js` that might be relevant, including `INITIAL_STATE`, `EMISSION_FACTORS`, `calculateTotalCO2`, `saveToLocalStorage`, and `loadFromLocalStorage`. I\'m now exploring how to represent the interface in an aesthetic manner.\n\n\n**Designing the UI and Code**\n\nI\'m now implementing the UI design for `/src/App.tsx`. I\'m going for a clean layout with a light gray background (`bg-slate-50`). The plan is to have a central display showing the state alongside an interactive panel to modify variables and immediately visualize the total CO2 calculation. I\'ll include a code block from `store.js` or explain the API. React states will track the current values, updating live and calling `saveToLocalStorage` on change. I\'m focusing on UI elegance and ensuring safety against infinite loops, and I\'m importing all the code from `./store.js`. Typescript is not complaining since `\"allowJs\": true`. I will use named imports.\n\n\n**Planning the Layout**\n\nI\'m now sketching out the visual structure. I envision a three-column layout: transport, food, and energy. Each section will have interactive elements (input fields or buttons) for user data, and a clear display of the current carbon footprint total. I\'m aiming for high contrast and a clean design for the \"Alltags-CO2-Rechner Kernlogik\" header. I will include a minimal badge to emphasize that this is a fully client-side prototype. I am also checking how to import `motion`.\n\n\n**Visualizing the Data**\n\nI\'m now focusing on how to represent the CO2 data. I\'m thinking of sliders or buttons for dietary choices (meat-rich vs. vegan days) and electricity consumption, along with their respective CO2 emissions. The main display will feature a large, animated numeral showing the total CO2 emissions in kilograms, styled with a dark slate color and a subtle colored guide for comparison. A save button will store the state to LocalStorage. I\'m also planning an interactive code viewer tab to display and annotate the `store.js` structure in a mock-editor style, which will allow people to copy code.\n\n\n**Verifying JavaScript Code**\n\nI\'ve decided to include the JavaScript code in a code box. The code serves as a basis for our later `store.js` module. I\'m verifying the emission factor calculations: `Auto`: 0.12, `\303\226PNV`: 0.03, `Fleisch`: 2.5, `Vegan`: 0.9, `Strom`: 0.42. I\'m also confirming the React 19 package imports and TypeScript compliance. I\'ve imported `Inter` font, and Tailwind CSS is correctly included. Finally, I\'ve started drafting `/src/App.tsx`. I will implement the React component next.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 45
      nanos: 630885130
    }
